<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="251" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,222,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">
<bibRefCitation author="Tanaka, S." box="[151,316,222,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" pagination="7 - 12" refId="ref5267" refString="Tanaka, S. (1917) Eleven new species of fish from Japan. Dobutsugaku Zasshi, 29, 7 - 12." type="journal article" year="1917">Tanaka (1917)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[444,665,222,247]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[444,665,222,247]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Chromis mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<typeStatus box="[785,883,222,247]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
collected off Goto Island, 
<collectingRegion box="[1199,1432,222,247]" country="Japan" name="Nagasaki" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Nagasaki Prefecture</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,218,259,282]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[553,704,259,283]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[553,704,259,283]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is brief, and not accompanied by an illustration. Two nominal species are currently regarded as synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[696,847,295,318]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[696,847,295,318]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Araga &amp; Yoshino" authorityName="Araga &amp; Yoshino" authorityYear="1975" box="[865,1219,294,319]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fraenatus">
<emphasis box="[865,1007,295,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. fraenatus</emphasis>
Araga &amp; Yoshino
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Masuda, H. &amp; Araga, C. &amp; Yoshino, T." pageId="2" pageNumber="251" refId="ref4871" refString="Masuda, H., Araga, C. &amp; Yoshino, T. (1975) Coastal fishes of Southern Japan. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, 379 pp." type="book" year="1975">
Masuda 
<emphasis box="[1370,1436,294,319]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">et al.,</emphasis>
1975
</bibRefCitation>
), type locality off Minabe, 
<collectingRegion box="[519,768,330,355]" country="Japan" name="Wakayama" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Wakayama Prefecture</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[780,847,331,354]" name="Japan" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Japan</collectingCountry>
; 
<taxonomicName authority="Allen 1976" authorityName="Allen" authorityYear="1976" box="[859,1225,330,355]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="megalopsis">
<emphasis box="[859,1089,330,355]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Chromis megalopsis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Allen, G. R." box="[1096,1225,330,355]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" pagination="133 - 144" refId="ref4278" refString="Allen, G. R. (1976) Two new species of damselfishes (Pomacentridae) from Western Australia. Records of the Western Australian Museum, 4, 133 - 144." type="journal article" year="1976">Allen 1976</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, type locality west of Bernier Island, Western Australia. Tanakaâ€™s 
<typeStatus box="[683,781,366,391]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[820,970,367,390]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[820,970,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently listed as lost by Fricke 
<emphasis box="[1379,1436,366,391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">et al.</emphasis>
(2019). However, we located the 
<typeStatus box="[520,618,402,427]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
in the Department of Zoology, University Museum, University of Tokyo, Tokyo (ZUMT 3627; 
<figureCitation box="[399,493,438,463]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1862,1884]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,667,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,662,1838]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chromis mirationis, ZUMT 3627, 74.3 mm SL, holotype. A: left lateral view; B: right pectoral axil; C: lower part of head showing posterior extent of free suborbital margin (indicated by arrow). Photos by H. Senou." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644450/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Figure 1</figureCitation>
). Conversely, the 
<typeStatus box="[702,800,438,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus box="[856,952,439,463]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Araga &amp; Yoshino" authorityYear="1975" box="[992,1132,439,463]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fraenatus">
<emphasis box="[992,1132,439,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. fraenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(SMBL 72067 and SMBL 73391, respectively) could not be located at in the collection of the Kyoto University Museum, Kyoto University (Dr Y. Kai, pers. comm.). Morphometric data for the 
<typeStatus box="[788,886,510,535]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[932,1085,511,534]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[932,1085,511,534]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are provided in 
<tableCitation box="[1286,1374,510,535]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="7.[151,239,152,175]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 1. Proportional measurements of type specimens of Chromis tingting sp. nov., and of the holotype of C. mirationis expressed as a percentage of the standard length." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF1890B3FF9CE054C9C7FF12800DC7A5" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" tableUuid="DF1890B3FF9CE054C9C7FF12800DC7A5">Table 1</tableCitation>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[151,260,546,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotypes</typeStatus>
of both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[355,504,547,571]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[355,504,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Araga &amp; Yoshino" authorityYear="1975" box="[559,698,547,571]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fraenatus">
<emphasis box="[559,698,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. fraenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Randall, J. E. &amp; Ida, H. &amp; Moyer, J. T." box="[919,1152,546,571]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" pagination="203 - 242" refId="ref5045" refString="Randall, J. E., Ida, H. &amp; Moyer, J. T. (1981) A review of the damselfishes of the genus Chromis from Japan &amp; Taiwan, with description of a new species. Japanese Journal of Ichthyology, 28, 203 - 242, 1 pl." type="journal article" year="1981">
Randall 
<emphasis box="[1014,1071,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">et al.</emphasis>
(1981)
</bibRefCitation>
who concluded that they were conspecific. We concur with this assessment, thus the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[905,1054,583,606]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[905,1054,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be applied to that species rather than to the species herein newly described. Diagnostic characters that clearly differentiate the two species are apparent in the 
<typeStatus box="[325,426,654,679]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">holotype</typeStatus>
, particularly the absence of a conspicuous large dark spot in the pectoral axil (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1420,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1862,1884]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,667,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,662,1838]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chromis mirationis, ZUMT 3627, 74.3 mm SL, holotype. A: left lateral view; B: right pectoral axil; C: lower part of head showing posterior extent of free suborbital margin (indicated by arrow). Photos by H. Senou." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644450/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Figure 1B</figureCitation>
), and more expansive free margin of the suborbital (extending well beyond vertical through posterior margin of pupil versus to vertical through middle of pupil; 
<figureCitation box="[640,765,726,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1862,1884]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,667,1830]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,662,1838]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chromis mirationis, ZUMT 3627, 74.3 mm SL, holotype. A: left lateral view; B: right pectoral axil; C: lower part of head showing posterior extent of free suborbital margin (indicated by arrow). Photos by H. Senou." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644450/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">Figures 1C</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation box="[823,839,727,751]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1121,1143]" captionTargetBox="[363,1108,245,1052]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,193,1099]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chromis tingting sp. nov., KPM-NI 30479, 53.6 mm SL, holotype, diagram of head. AN, anterior nostril; CSO, crescent opening of supraorbital canal; PN, posterior nostril. Arrow indicates posterior extent of free margin of suborbital. Exposed scales shown in grey." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2644454/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">3</figureCitation>
). Although Tanaka did not mention the lateral stripe that characterizes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1917" box="[352,500,763,787]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mirationis">
<emphasis box="[352,500,763,787]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. mirationis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this may be weakly developed in large adults (such as Araga &amp; Yoshinoâ€™s 91.0 mm SL 
<typeStatus box="[190,286,799,823]" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Araga &amp; Yoshino" authorityYear="1975" box="[324,463,799,823]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Chromis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="251" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fraenatus">
<emphasis box="[324,463,799,823]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="251">C. fraenatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
